Michael Jordan in "The Last Dance."
Isiah Thomas tells his side of the story, Jordan sloughs it off; all these years later, there's clearly no love lost between the two.
Jordan didn't start winning championships until he learned the value of a team, and Hehir takes that message to heart.
"The Last Dance" shows the best dances are done with a partner, or in this case, several.
